WEBVTT

00:00:12.583 --> 00:00:15.667
"April 8, 2023"       "Floor 11: Taft"
Here's to us, the Moonlit Black Cats!

00:00:16.542 --> 00:00:17.625
Cheers!

00:00:19.208 --> 00:00:23.500
And here's to Kirito, the
man who saved our lives!

00:00:23.750 --> 00:00:25.125
Cheers!

00:00:25.125 --> 00:00:27.083
Ch-Cheers...

00:00:27.292 --> 00:00:28.042
Thanks.

00:00:28.042 --> 00:00:29.625
--Thanks!
--You saved us.

00:00:29.625 --> 00:00:30.625
Thank you.

00:00:30.625 --> 00:00:31.833
Thank you so much.

00:00:31.833 --> 00:00:33.292
It was nothing.

00:00:33.875 --> 00:00:35.958
I was really scared.

00:00:35.958 --> 00:00:39.083
So when you came to save me,
it made me so happy.

00:00:39.083 --> 00:00:40.417
S-Sure...

00:00:40.417 --> 00:00:42.250
Um, Kirito...

00:00:42.250 --> 00:00:44.500
I know this is really rude to ask,

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:46.333
but about what level are you?

00:00:47.583 --> 00:00:49.417
Level 20 or so.

00:00:50.625 --> 00:00:52.583
You're not that much
higher than us,

00:00:52.583 --> 00:00:54.417
and yet you're
a solo player!

00:00:54.417 --> 00:00:56.958
Keita, you don't need
to be so polite.

00:00:56.958 --> 00:01:00.333
I'm solo, but that means I'm
targeting isolated enemies.

00:01:00.333 --> 00:01:01.583
It isn't that efficient.

00:01:01.583 --> 00:01:03.667
Oh... Oh, I see.

00:01:03.667 --> 00:01:06.792
In that case, Kirito, sorry to spring
this on you all of a sudden,

00:01:06.792 --> 00:01:09.375
but how about joining our guild?

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:14.375
The only player who can handle the
vanguard is our mace user, Tetsuo.

00:01:14.375 --> 00:01:16.958
This one's name is Sachi.

00:01:16.958 --> 00:01:19.292
I'm thinking that she switch to
be a sword-and-shield wielder

00:01:19.292 --> 00:01:21.375
so she can cover
the front line.

00:01:21.375 --> 00:01:24.375
But she says that she
isn't really sure how.

00:01:24.375 --> 00:01:27.042
Think you could coach her?

00:01:27.042 --> 00:01:29.625
Come on! Don't make me
sound so useless.

00:01:30.667 --> 00:01:35.833
I'd be too scared if you suddenly
tell me to fight in the vanguard.

00:01:35.833 --> 00:01:37.875
Just hide behind your shield.

00:01:37.875 --> 00:01:41.333
I swear! You've always
been such a scaredy-cat.

00:01:43.792 --> 00:01:50.375
See, in real life, all of our guild members
belong to our school's PC Research Club.

00:01:50.375 --> 00:01:52.667
Oh, hey, don't worry though...

00:01:52.667 --> 00:01:55.292
You're sure to fit in right
away, Kirito. For sure!

00:01:55.292 --> 00:01:56.292
Right?

00:02:02.167 --> 00:02:03.167
Then...

00:02:03.625 --> 00:02:07.000
I guess I'll join you
guys after all...

00:02:08.042 --> 00:02:09.375
Glad to work with you.

00:02:12.917 --> 00:02:15.500
--Let's all do our best, okay?
--I'm Sasamaru. Glad you joined us!

00:02:27.375 --> 00:02:31.792
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:02:32.125 --> 00:02:37.625
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:02:38.042 --> 00:02:48.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:48.875 --> 00:02:53.875
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:54.208 --> 00:02:58.583
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:58.917 --> 00:03:01.292
<i>Out of control</i>

00:03:01.625 --> 00:03:06.875
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:03:07.208 --> 00:03:12.042
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:03:12.375 --> 00:03:18.542
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:03:18.875 --> 00:03:22.500
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:03:22.875 --> 00:03:27.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:03:28.167 --> 00:03:33.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:03:34.750 --> 00:03:37.208
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:03:37.542 --> 00:03:42.917
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:46.042 --> 00:03:50.042
"Red-Nosed Reindeer"

00:03:51.042 --> 00:03:54.292
"May 9, 2023"       "Floor 20: Sunlit Forest"

00:04:01.542 --> 00:04:03.833
Sachi, step back for now!

00:04:11.083 --> 00:04:12.583
Tetsuo, switch!

00:04:12.583 --> 00:04:13.583
Right!

00:04:18.792 --> 00:04:19.625
"Scythe of Killer Mantis"

00:04:20.542 --> 00:04:21.833
All right!

00:04:23.083 --> 00:04:25.000
You did it!

00:04:26.958 --> 00:04:30.000
So an Assault Team made it
through floor 28...

00:04:30.333 --> 00:04:31.917
That's amazing!

00:04:32.375 --> 00:04:34.083
Hey, Kirito.

00:04:34.083 --> 00:04:37.042
What is it that sets the Assault
Teams apart from us?

00:04:37.750 --> 00:04:39.500
Information, maybe?

00:04:39.500 --> 00:04:44.875
They know all the most efficient ways
to get EXP, and they don't share them.

00:04:46.208 --> 00:04:48.875
Well, I'm sure that's
got to be part of it.

00:04:48.875 --> 00:04:51.250
But I think it's willpower.

00:04:51.250 --> 00:04:52.250
Willpower?

00:04:53.625 --> 00:04:59.042
You could say it's how determined you are
to protect your friends... No, all the players.

00:04:59.042 --> 00:05:04.500
Now, we are still protected, but
I think my will's just as strong.

00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:08.208
Of course, our friends' safety
is our first priority.

00:05:08.208 --> 00:05:13.208
But someday, we want to join the
ranks of the Assault Team too.

00:05:13.875 --> 00:05:15.000
I see.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:16.167
You're right.

00:05:16.708 --> 00:05:18.042
Heh, maybe...

00:05:18.417 --> 00:05:21.292
Hey, leader, you're so cool!

00:05:21.500 --> 00:05:22.500
Come on...

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:26.708
Joining the ranks of the Holy Dragon
Alliance or the Knights of the Blood Oath?

00:05:26.708 --> 00:05:28.125
What about it?

00:05:28.125 --> 00:05:30.333
We might as well set
our goal high.

00:05:30.333 --> 00:05:32.458
First, we're all gonna
hit level 30, okay?

00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:34.167
That's impossible!

00:05:34.167 --> 00:05:38.458
<i>If the Black Cats do make rapid</i>
<i>strides and reach the front lines,</i>

00:05:38.958 --> 00:05:43.542
<i>Keita's ideals could change the insular</i>
<i>atmosphere of the Assault Teams.</i>

00:05:48.625 --> 00:05:50.667
I have an announcement
to make, everyone.

00:05:50.958 --> 00:05:56.167
Um... As of our last hunt,
we've saved 200,000 Col!

00:05:57.625 --> 00:06:00.833
Buying our own house won't be
just a dream pretty soon.

00:06:00.833 --> 00:06:03.458
Hey, why don't we upgrade
Sachi's equipment?

00:06:03.458 --> 00:06:04.833
Good idea.

00:06:04.833 --> 00:06:07.833
I'm fine with what I have.

00:06:07.833 --> 00:06:09.583
Don't be shy.

00:06:09.583 --> 00:06:12.958
It wouldn't be fair to make Kirito take
the vanguard forever, you know.

00:06:13.667 --> 00:06:14.708
I'm sorry.

00:06:15.083 --> 00:06:16.792
I don't mind.

00:06:16.792 --> 00:06:17.917
Don't worry about it.

00:06:17.917 --> 00:06:19.500
Sorry, Kirito...

00:06:19.833 --> 00:06:22.375
Sachi, I know it's hard
to switch jobs.

00:06:22.375 --> 00:06:24.292
But you know what?
You're almost there.

00:06:24.292 --> 00:06:25.583
Let's all do our best!

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:27.500
Yeah.

00:06:36.167 --> 00:06:38.917
"May 16, 2023"       "Floor 28: Wolf Plains"

00:06:45.375 --> 00:06:46.375
Klein...

00:07:00.625 --> 00:07:02.250
Hey, it's you, Kirito!

00:07:02.250 --> 00:07:04.292
You guys, clean up the
rest of the trash mobs.

00:07:04.292 --> 00:07:05.667
Sure.

00:07:05.667 --> 00:07:08.250
I was thinking I hadn't
seen you for a while.

00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:10.542
You're out leveling
this late at night?

00:07:11.625 --> 00:07:13.042
Hey... that mark...

00:07:13.625 --> 00:07:15.083
Did you join a guild?

00:07:15.083 --> 00:07:16.792
Yeah, sort of...

00:07:17.125 --> 00:07:19.417
Hey, we can move on now!

00:07:21.875 --> 00:07:23.292
See you.

00:07:23.292 --> 00:07:24.292
Sure.

00:07:25.833 --> 00:07:30.250
For crying out loud...
It's still bugging you?

00:07:38.417 --> 00:07:39.792
<i>"This is Keita.</i>

00:07:39.792 --> 00:07:42.375
<i>Sachi went off somewhere</i>
<i>and still hasn't returned.</i>

00:07:42.375 --> 00:07:44.625
<i>We're heading to</i>
<i>the dungeon area.</i>

00:07:44.625 --> 00:07:47.125
<i>If you learn anything,</i>
<i>let me know."</i>

00:07:48.125 --> 00:07:49.167
Sachi...

00:07:51.917 --> 00:07:52.958
"Seek Enemy"
"Track"
"Launch Sword"

00:08:10.208 --> 00:08:11.250
Sachi!

00:08:12.958 --> 00:08:14.167
Kirito?

00:08:14.167 --> 00:08:15.958
Everyone's worried.

00:08:21.958 --> 00:08:23.417
Hey, Kirito...

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:27.250
Let's run away together.

00:08:27.250 --> 00:08:29.583
Run away from what?

00:08:30.375 --> 00:08:33.417
From this town, the monsters...

00:08:33.750 --> 00:08:35.750
From the Black Cats...

00:08:36.500 --> 00:08:38.417
From Sword Art Online.

00:08:39.250 --> 00:08:41.792
A-Are you talking about
double suicide?

00:08:43.708 --> 00:08:45.542
That might be okay too.

00:08:46.292 --> 00:08:48.417
No, I'm sorry.

00:08:48.417 --> 00:08:49.625
That was a lie.

00:08:49.625 --> 00:08:51.458
If I had the courage to die,

00:08:51.458 --> 00:08:54.125
I wouldn't hide within the
safety of the town, would I?

00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:59.083
Hey, why can't we
leave this place?

00:09:00.542 --> 00:09:03.667
Why do we really have to die,
even though it's a game?

00:09:04.250 --> 00:09:06.292
What's the point of all this?

00:09:08.083 --> 00:09:11.250
I don't think there is a point.

00:09:14.250 --> 00:09:17.167
I'm afraid of dying.

00:09:19.083 --> 00:09:21.208
You're afraid of dying?

00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:26.792
I'm so scared I haven't
been able to sleep lately...

00:09:28.917 --> 00:09:30.458
You won't die.

00:09:31.875 --> 00:09:33.083
Really?

00:09:33.083 --> 00:09:35.083
How can you say for sure?

00:09:35.750 --> 00:09:38.375
The Black Cats are strong
enough as a guild.

00:09:38.917 --> 00:09:41.542
Our margin of safety is
well above average.

00:09:42.042 --> 00:09:44.708
And there's both
Tetsuo and me.

00:09:44.708 --> 00:09:47.292
So you don't need to force
yourself to the front ranks.

00:09:47.583 --> 00:09:49.958
I really don't have to die?

00:09:50.375 --> 00:09:52.333
I can go back to
reality someday?

00:09:52.708 --> 00:09:53.667
Yeah.

00:09:53.667 --> 00:09:54.833
You aren't going to die.

00:09:55.417 --> 00:09:58.792
I'm sure they'll beat
this game eventually.

00:10:13.792 --> 00:10:14.792
Come in.

00:10:17.917 --> 00:10:19.208
I'm sorry.

00:10:19.208 --> 00:10:21.333
I just couldn't get to sleep.

00:10:23.833 --> 00:10:26.083
<i>If I stay in this guild,</i>
<i>she'll be safe.</i>

00:10:26.500 --> 00:10:29.167
<i>Someday, we'll be able to</i>
<i>go back to the real world.</i>

00:10:30.333 --> 00:10:34.500
<i>There are lots of players</i>
<i>like Sachi who fear death.</i>

00:10:34.958 --> 00:10:39.458
<i>But they still laugh, cry, and try with</i>
<i>all their might to live in this world.</i>

00:10:40.750 --> 00:10:43.000
<i>I've never even thought about it...</i>

00:10:43.333 --> 00:10:44.333
Kirito?

00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:46.958
It's okay.

00:10:46.958 --> 00:10:49.083
You're going to survive.
I promise.

00:10:55.167 --> 00:10:58.625
<i>Because I'm going to protect</i>
<i>you all, no matter what.</i>

00:11:02.375 --> 00:11:03.833
Okay, I'm off!

00:11:04.292 --> 00:11:06.250
Teleport: Town of Beginnings.

00:11:09.792 --> 00:11:13.958
I didn't know buying your own
home would be so exciting.

00:11:13.958 --> 00:11:15.625
You sound like an old man!

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:24.417
Hey, let's go raise some cash
while Keita's buying the house.

00:11:24.417 --> 00:11:26.125
Oh! Are we going
to buy furniture?

00:11:26.125 --> 00:11:28.667
In that case, want to
go up to the dungeon?

00:11:29.375 --> 00:11:31.917
Shouldn't our usual hunting
grounds be good enough?

00:11:32.250 --> 00:11:34.375
We can make more in
a short time up there.

00:11:34.667 --> 00:11:36.917
At our levels, it should be safe!

00:11:39.542 --> 00:11:40.750
"June 12, 2023"       "Floor 27: Dungeon"

00:11:40.750 --> 00:11:43.542
"June 12, 2023"       "Floor 27: Dungeon"
Didn't I tell you? This'll be a breeze for us.

00:11:43.833 --> 00:11:46.708
We might be able to reach
the front lines soon!

00:11:46.708 --> 00:11:48.458
Heck, yeah!

00:11:55.917 --> 00:11:58.375
<i>A hidden door...</i>
<i>in a place like this?</i>

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:03.708
A treasure chest!

00:12:05.833 --> 00:12:06.833
W-Wait!

00:12:21.625 --> 00:12:22.833
It's a trap!

00:12:23.542 --> 00:12:25.375
Everyone, let's get out of here!

00:12:25.375 --> 00:12:26.958
Teleport: Taft!

00:12:27.708 --> 00:12:28.833
Teleport: Taft!

00:12:28.833 --> 00:12:30.875
We can't use our crystals!

00:12:31.417 --> 00:12:33.000
So this is a crystal-nullification area?

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.292
Tetsuo!

00:12:53.292 --> 00:12:54.500
Damn it!

00:13:09.208 --> 00:13:10.208
Sachi!

00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:12.750
Kirito!

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:15.000
Sachi!

00:13:35.458 --> 00:13:38.958
"December 24, 2023"       "Floor 49: Mugien"

00:13:44.917 --> 00:13:48.375
Lately, you've been taking big
risks with your level raising.

00:13:48.833 --> 00:13:51.083
Did you get any new information?

00:13:51.542 --> 00:13:53.958
Nothing worth charging money for.

00:13:54.458 --> 00:13:56.542
You're giving information
brokers a bad name.

00:13:56.542 --> 00:14:00.000
This wasn't in the beta test.
It's a first-time event.

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:02.250
There's no way to get information.

00:14:02.875 --> 00:14:04.375
On Christmas Eve...

00:14:04.375 --> 00:14:06.042
In other words, late tonight,

00:14:06.042 --> 00:14:09.458
the event boss, "Nicholas the
Renegade," will appear.

00:14:09.833 --> 00:14:11.833
Beneath a certain fir tree.

00:14:12.667 --> 00:14:16.250
The leading guilds are
searching frantically for it.

00:14:18.583 --> 00:14:21.083
You have an idea
where it is, don't you?

00:14:21.083 --> 00:14:22.208
Maybe.

00:14:22.625 --> 00:14:24.708
You're seriously going
to try and solo it?

00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:33.708
<i>In this world, the dead</i>
<i>can never return.</i>

00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:38.083
<i>But there's a rumor that</i>
<i>Nicholas the Renegade</i>

00:14:38.917 --> 00:14:42.667
<i>will drop an item that can</i>
<i>revive a dead player.</i>

00:14:44.667 --> 00:14:47.708
<i>If I try and fight him alone,</i>

00:14:48.458 --> 00:14:49.708
<i>I'll probably die.</i>

00:14:50.250 --> 00:14:52.125
<i>I'll die in a place where</i>
<i>no one will see me,</i>

00:14:52.792 --> 00:14:55.125
<i>leaving nothing behind.</i>

00:14:55.583 --> 00:14:57.125
You were a beater...

00:14:57.125 --> 00:14:59.583
You never had any right
to get involved with us!

00:15:11.792 --> 00:15:12.917
<i>That's right.</i>

00:15:13.375 --> 00:15:14.542
<i>I...</i>

00:15:14.958 --> 00:15:16.833
<i>My arrogance...</i>

00:15:16.833 --> 00:15:18.833
...<i>killed you all.</i>

00:15:20.292 --> 00:15:24.292
<i>If only I hadn't kept</i>
<i>my level secret...</i>

00:15:28.167 --> 00:15:31.792
"Floor 35: Forest Maze"
<i>If I can defeat Nicholas,</i>

00:15:31.792 --> 00:15:34.042
<i>Sachi's soul will return,</i>

00:15:34.042 --> 00:15:36.917
<i>and I'll be able to</i>
<i>hear her last words.</i>

00:15:40.750 --> 00:15:43.042
<i>Whatever words she</i>
<i>uses to curse me,</i>

00:15:43.042 --> 00:15:45.333
<i>I've got to accept them.</i>

00:15:57.625 --> 00:15:58.542
Yo.

00:15:58.542 --> 00:16:00.083
You followed me?

00:16:00.083 --> 00:16:01.542
Well, yeah.

00:16:01.542 --> 00:16:03.167
Are you after the revival item?

00:16:03.833 --> 00:16:04.958
Yeah.

00:16:04.958 --> 00:16:08.625
Don't risk your life over what
might be a bogus rumor.

00:16:10.333 --> 00:16:12.625
This death game is for real.

00:16:13.292 --> 00:16:15.667
The moment our HP drops to zero,

00:16:15.667 --> 00:16:17.333
our brains in the real world--

00:16:17.333 --> 00:16:18.458
Shut up.

00:16:19.458 --> 00:16:22.250
Enough with your
reckless solo raids!

00:16:22.250 --> 00:16:23.833
Join us...

00:16:24.083 --> 00:16:27.583
Whoever gets it to drop the revival item
keeps it, no hard feelings.

00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:29.042
That should be fair enough, right?

00:16:30.042 --> 00:16:33.333
Then there'd be no point.

00:16:33.750 --> 00:16:35.083
I have to do it myself.

00:16:37.417 --> 00:16:42.167
I can't let you die here, Kirito!

00:16:47.667 --> 00:16:50.125
So, you were being
followed too, Klein.

00:16:50.917 --> 00:16:52.000
Looks that way.

00:16:52.583 --> 00:16:54.542
Damn! The Holy Dragon Alliance?

00:16:54.542 --> 00:16:57.833
They'll do anything, no matter
how risky, for a rare item.

00:16:57.833 --> 00:16:58.917
What should we do?

00:17:00.167 --> 00:17:01.208
I...

00:17:03.583 --> 00:17:05.000
Damn it!

00:17:05.167 --> 00:17:06.708
Go, Kirito!

00:17:06.708 --> 00:17:07.667
Klein...

00:17:07.667 --> 00:17:10.458
Go on! We'll hold them off!

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:53.458
Shut up.

00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:22.833
Kirito!

00:18:26.458 --> 00:18:27.958
H-Hey...

00:18:27.958 --> 00:18:30.042
That's the revival item.

00:18:31.458 --> 00:18:32.500
Let me see.

00:18:33.083 --> 00:18:34.958
"The target player..."

00:18:34.958 --> 00:18:35.917
"(WITHIN 10 SECONDS)"

00:18:36.167 --> 00:18:37.292
"Within 10 seconds"?

00:18:37.917 --> 00:18:41.708
Use it on the next person
who dies before your eyes.

00:18:53.208 --> 00:18:54.250
Kirito...

00:18:55.208 --> 00:18:56.333
Kirito!

00:18:57.875 --> 00:19:00.667
You... You've got to live!

00:19:01.375 --> 00:19:04.250
Survive until the end, please...

00:19:10.083 --> 00:19:11.167
See you.

00:19:31.583 --> 00:19:32.708
Sachi?

00:19:44.625 --> 00:19:46.833
<i>Merry Christmas, Kirito.</i>

00:19:48.875 --> 00:19:51.083
<i>By the time you hear this,</i>

00:19:51.083 --> 00:19:53.250
<i>I'm guessing I'll be dead.</i>

00:19:53.958 --> 00:19:56.000
<i>How can I explain it...</i>

00:19:56.458 --> 00:19:59.167
Um, you see...
To tell you the truth,

00:19:59.167 --> 00:20:02.333
I never really wanted to leave
the Town of Beginnings.

00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.625
But if I fight with that attitude,

00:20:05.625 --> 00:20:07.833
I'm sure I'll end up
dying one day, right?

00:20:08.542 --> 00:20:10.500
And it's no one's fault.

00:20:10.500 --> 00:20:12.333
It's my own problem.

00:20:13.375 --> 00:20:16.917
Kirito, ever since that night,
you've been telling me

00:20:16.917 --> 00:20:19.917
night after night
that I won't die.

00:20:20.500 --> 00:20:25.042
So if I ever get killed, I know
that you'll really blame yourself.

00:20:25.542 --> 00:20:28.375
That's why I decided
to record this.

00:20:29.167 --> 00:20:34.000
<i>Also, I know how powerful</i>
<i>you really are.</i>

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:37.000
<i>You see, a while ago</i>
<i>I peeked accidentally.</i>

00:20:37.875 --> 00:20:40.375
<i>I thought really hard about why</i>

00:20:40.375 --> 00:20:43.125
<i>you would hide your level</i>
<i>and fight with us,</i>

00:20:43.125 --> 00:20:46.833
<i>but I never did figure it out.</i>

00:20:47.917 --> 00:20:53.333
<i>But when I found out how strong</i>
<i>you really were, it made me so happy.</i>

00:20:53.333 --> 00:20:55.167
<i>I felt so relieved.</i>

00:20:55.500 --> 00:20:57.792
<i>So even if I die,</i>

00:20:58.333 --> 00:21:00.292
<i>you do your best to</i>
<i>go on living, okay?</i>

00:21:00.708 --> 00:21:03.458
<i>Live to see the end</i>
<i>of this world,</i>

00:21:03.458 --> 00:21:05.500
<i>and to see why it</i>
<i>was ever created...</i>

00:21:05.500 --> 00:21:08.208
<i>The reason why a weakling</i>
<i>like me ended up here...</i>

00:21:08.833 --> 00:21:12.250
<i>And please find the reason</i>
<i>why you and I met.</i>

00:21:13.458 --> 00:21:15.542
<i>That's what I wish.</i>

00:21:16.458 --> 00:21:18.458
Looks like there's still
plenty of time left.

00:21:18.917 --> 00:21:22.333
All right, since it's Christmas,
I'll sing you a song, okay?

00:21:56.375 --> 00:21:57.875
<i>Bye, Kirito.</i>

00:21:58.458 --> 00:22:01.875
<i>I'm so glad that I met you,</i>

00:22:02.542 --> 00:22:04.000
<i>that I could be with you.</i>

00:22:05.792 --> 00:22:06.875
<i>Thank you.</i>

00:22:07.250 --> 00:22:08.333
<i>Goodbye.</i>

00:22:30.042 --> 00:22:41.542
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:53.375
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.750 --> 00:22:59.292
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.625 --> 00:23:05.125
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.542 --> 00:23:10.542
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.875 --> 00:23:15.833
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.167 --> 00:23:22.667
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:26.625
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.167 --> 00:23:33.875
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.208 --> 00:23:39.667
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:46.208
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:53.110
Next Time: "The Black Swordsman."
